msgid "Tasmā vineyya maccheraṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.23:7.2"
msgid "dajjā dānaṃ malābhibhū; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.23:7.3"
msgid "Puññāni paralokasmiṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.23:7.4"
msgid "patiṭṭhā honti pāṇinan’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc8
#. VAR: sirī → serī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn2.23:8.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbāhaṃ, bhante, sirī nāma rājā ahosiṃ dāyako dānapati dānassa vaṇṇavādī. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, sir, I was a king named Serī, a giver, a donor, who praised giving. "

# NOTE: I’m not sure why BB has “had gifts given” here; diyittha is aorist passive, not causative. Lit: “of that me gift was given …”
msgctxt "sn2.23:8.2"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, catūsu dvāresu dānaṃ dīyittha samaṇabrāhmaṇakapaṇaddhikavanibbakayācakānaṃ. "
msgstr "I gave gifts at the four gates to ascetics and brahmins, to paupers, vagrants, travelers, and beggars. "

#. VAR: itthāgāraṃ upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca → itthāgārā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn2.23:8.3"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, bhante, itthāgāraṃ upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the ladies of my harem approached me and said, "

#. VAR: devassa kho → devasseva kho (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn2.23:8.4"
msgid "‘devassa kho dānaṃ dīyati; amhākaṃ dānaṃ na dīyati. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty gives gifts, but we don’t. "

msgctxt "sn2.23:8.5"
msgid "Sādhu mayampi devaṃ nissāya dānāni dadeyyāma, puññāni kareyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Your Majesty, please support us to give gifts and make merit.’ "

msgctxt "sn2.23:8.6"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "sn2.23:8.7"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khosmi dāyako dānapati dānassa vaṇṇavādī. "
msgstr "‘I’m a giver, a donor, who praises giving. "

msgctxt "sn2.23:8.8"
msgid "Dānaṃ dassāmāti vadante kinti vadeyyan’ti? "
msgstr "When they say, “We would give gifts”, what am I to say?’ "

msgctxt "sn2.23:8.9"
msgid "So khvāhaṃ, bhante, paṭhamaṃ dvāraṃ itthāgārassa adāsiṃ. "
msgstr "And so I gave the first gate to the ladies of my harem. "

# NOTE: BB has “returned” for patikkamati, which I think misses the point. I’m not clear what’s it’s meant to mean, either. patikkamati is used in two main senses: to return, and to dwindle. In the latter sense it’s found in the stock passage on the reduction of suffering for one who is ill. The point here is that as the king assigned his gates one by one for others to give, his own giving diminished until he had to send gifts outside the town.
msgctxt "sn2.23:8.10"
msgid "Tattha itthāgārassa dānaṃ dīyittha; mama dānaṃ paṭikkami. "
msgstr "There they gave gifts, while my own giving dwindled. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.135, sc9
msgctxt "sn2.23:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, bhante, khattiyā anuyantā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then my aristocrat vassals approached me and said, "

msgctxt "sn2.23:9.2"
msgid "‘devassa kho dānaṃ dīyati; itthāgārassa dānaṃ dīyati; amhākaṃ dānaṃ na dīyati. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty gives gifts, the ladies of your harem give gifts, but we don’t. "

msgctxt "sn2.23:9.3"
msgid "Sādhu mayampi devaṃ nissāya dānāni dadeyyāma, puññāni kareyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Your Majesty, please support us to give gifts and make merit.’ "

msgctxt "sn2.23:9.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "sn2.23:9.5"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khosmi dāyako dānapati dānassa vaṇṇavādī. "
msgstr "‘I’m a giver, a donor, who praises giving. "

msgctxt "sn2.23:9.6"
msgid "Dānaṃ dassāmāti vadante kinti vadeyyan’ti? "
msgstr "When they say, “We would give gifts”, what am I to say?’ "

msgctxt "sn2.23:9.7"
msgid "So khvāhaṃ, bhante, dutiyaṃ dvāraṃ khattiyānaṃ anuyantānaṃ adāsiṃ. "
msgstr "And so I gave the second gate to my aristocrat vassals. "

msgctxt "sn2.23:9.8"
msgid "Tattha khattiyānaṃ anuyantānaṃ dānaṃ dīyittha, mama dānaṃ paṭikkami. "
msgstr "There they gave gifts, while my own giving dwindled. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.59, sc10
msgctxt "sn2.23:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, bhante, balakāyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then my troops approached me and said, "

msgctxt "sn2.23:10.2"
msgid "‘devassa kho dānaṃ dīyati; itthāgārassa dānaṃ dīyati; khattiyānaṃ anuyantānaṃ dānaṃ dīyati; amhākaṃ dānaṃ na dīyati. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty gives gifts, the ladies of your harem give gifts, your aristocrat vassals give gifts, but we don’t. "

msgctxt "sn2.23:10.3"
msgid "Sādhu mayampi devaṃ nissāya dānāni dadeyyāma, puññāni kareyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Your Majesty, please support us to give gifts and make merit.’ "

msgctxt "sn2.23:10.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "sn2.23:10.5"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khosmi dāyako dānapati dānassa vaṇṇavādī. "
msgstr "‘I’m a giver, a donor, who praises giving. "

msgctxt "sn2.23:10.6"
msgid "Dānaṃ dassāmāti vadante kinti vadeyyan’ti? "
msgstr "When they say, “We would give gifts”, what am I to say?’ "

msgctxt "sn2.23:10.7"
msgid "So khvāhaṃ, bhante, tatiyaṃ dvāraṃ balakāyassa adāsiṃ. "
msgstr "And so I gave the third gate to my troops. "

msgctxt "sn2.23:10.8"
msgid "Tattha balakāyassa dānaṃ dīyittha, mama dānaṃ paṭikkami. "
msgstr "There they gave gifts, while my own giving dwindled. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.136, sc11
msgctxt "sn2.23:11.1"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, bhante, brāhmaṇagahapatikā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then my brahmins and householders approached me and said, "

msgctxt "sn2.23:11.2"
msgid "‘devassa kho dānaṃ dīyati; itthāgārassa dānaṃ dīyati; khattiyānaṃ anuyantānaṃ dānaṃ dīyati; balakāyassa dānaṃ dīyati; amhākaṃ dānaṃ na dīyati. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty gives gifts, the ladies of your harem give gifts, your aristocrat vassals give gifts, your troops give gifts, but we don’t. "

